And when it was physically presented to me,

18:03.440 --> 18:05.920
it was like, nothing like I thought he would look.

18:05.920 --> 18:08.120
He actually didn't even exchange pictures.

18:08.120 --> 18:11.120
Because of that, because I didn't think it mattered.

18:11.120 --> 18:12.320
That it's of matters.

18:12.320 --> 18:13.960
That it matters a lot.

18:13.960 --> 18:18.120
So I just say, it's such a way to still be there

18:18.120 --> 18:19.240
after 10 years.

18:19.240 --> 18:21.600
I have to say, it's a different kind of work.

18:21.600 --> 18:26.120
And in this day and age, I think that we've become,

18:26.120 --> 18:27.680
it's interesting, I think we've become

18:27.680 --> 18:30.000
people who are willing to do the kind of work

18:30.000 --> 18:32.680
that we would never, my parents would never have done.

18:32.680 --> 18:35.000
I mean, when you told me, when you said your parents met,

18:35.000 --> 18:36.480
and that's like, who does that?

18:36.480 --> 18:37.760
Like 20 years ago.

18:37.760 --> 18:40.000
I mean, it was a very different way of courting.

18:40.000 --> 18:42.640
And what's also fascinating is, how do we,

18:42.640 --> 18:44.440
and this might be a question to, I mean,

18:44.440 --> 18:54.200
how do we acclimate to using different phenomenology

18:54.200 --> 19:00.600
around instinct, which meaning somebody online is not,

19:00.600 --> 19:04.240
it's very different than having an instinct for somebody

19:04.240 --> 19:07.760
that you've met at a party, for instance.

19:07.760 --> 19:13.160
So I think one of the ways that online dating makes a difference

19:13.160 --> 19:17.440
is that you are sort of meeting an avatar in a person

19:17.440 --> 19:18.920
before you meet a person themselves.

19:18.920 --> 19:21.440
And one of the many results of that

19:21.440 --> 19:24.280
is that you invent an idea in your head of what he or she

19:24.280 --> 19:25.720
is like.

19:25.720 --> 19:27.040
And then, of course, at some point,

19:27.040 --> 19:28.200
you have to actually go meet them,

19:28.200 --> 19:32.800
and you have to sort of align those two things.

19:32.800 --> 19:36.400
And for some people, that can be a lot of disappointment.

19:36.400 --> 19:38.840
Because if the fantasy becomes very intense,

19:38.840 --> 19:42.040
then you ultimately have to reconcile the person with the fantasy,

19:42.040 --> 19:44.600
and that can be a disappointing process.

19:44.600 --> 19:46.520
But I think that's part of a learning curve thing.

19:46.520 --> 19:49.200
I think the people who do online dating for a while,

19:49.200 --> 19:52.840
they learn hopefully to get past that.

19:52.840 --> 19:54.440
I was saying to Lucy before we started

19:54.440 --> 19:58.520
that I think one of the great things that online dating is

19:58.520 --> 20:02.760
doing is that it is presenting people with some opportunities

20:02.760 --> 20:04.440
to fail.

20:04.440 --> 20:06.800
At least they're getting out there and meeting people

20:06.800 --> 20:10.280
and having relationships and having failed relationships

20:10.280 --> 20:13.040
and hopefully learning from them and hopefully making

20:13.040 --> 20:17.160
a better selection down the road as a result.

20:17.160 --> 20:19.160
