30:56.160 --> 30:58.400
I think that's the problem to begin with.

30:58.400 --> 31:00.960
And I fall in love with people that I'm not supposed to fall

31:00.960 --> 31:04.280
in love with, but by, in terms of what I think I like

31:04.280 --> 31:07.160
or I desire and much of it has to do with desire.

31:07.160 --> 31:09.880
I also think that if it's real love,

31:09.880 --> 31:12.720
there has to be a spiritual element to it.

31:12.720 --> 31:14.840
In other words, one of the best, but believe it or not,

31:14.840 --> 31:17.960
the best definition I've ever heard for this is by Scott Peck,

31:17.960 --> 31:19.840
who's not my favorite writer.

31:19.840 --> 31:24.320
But he said this great thing that love was being engaged

31:24.320 --> 31:26.760
in the spiritual progress of somebody else

31:26.760 --> 31:30.320
without insisting that they satisfy you.

31:30.320 --> 31:33.520
And I think, and that definition, it seems to me,

31:33.520 --> 31:37.480
could be carried over in a wide array of many different things

31:37.480 --> 31:38.320
that happen in a way.

31:38.320 --> 31:40.840
It could be physical or emotional or, I mean,

31:40.840 --> 31:44.800
I think that covers a lot of ground, even sexually.

31:44.800 --> 31:46.440
I think it could cover ground.

31:46.440 --> 31:50.440
But sat the idea of getting something back in a relation,

31:50.440 --> 31:54.000
in a love relationship, I think is where it gets screwy.

31:54.000 --> 31:54.880
I really do.

31:54.880 --> 31:57.880
I mean, and particularly when you have love

31:57.880 --> 32:00.560
for something that is not a person.

32:00.560 --> 32:02.520
I mean, I love many, many things in the world

32:02.520 --> 32:03.360
that have nothing.

